# Creating a `guide.mjs` Media Blueprint

Every guide directory that needs screenshots or video must have a `guides/{guide-name}/guide.mjs` blueprint. The Harmony Docs Studio CLI reads this file to know what to capture.

## Step 1 — Read the MDX first

Open the guide's `.mdx` file. Look for `{/* IMAGE: ... */}` comments — these mark exactly where screenshots are needed:

```mdx
{/* IMAGE: People data table with toolbar → /guides/managing-people/screenshots/people-list.png | UI: frontend-app/src/routes/people/index.tsx | Route: /people */}
```

Each comment gives you: description, output path (→ filename), and the app route. Create one target per IMAGE comment.

## File location & structure

```
guides/{guide-name}/
  guide.mjs          ← blueprint goes here
  {guide-name}.mdx
  screenshots/       ← auto-created by capture script
```

## Imports

```js
// For most guides (navigates to app pages)
import { BASE_URL } from "../_utilities/screenshot-shared.mjs";
import { clickWithCursor } from "../_utilities/video/video-cursor.mjs";

// For dashboard/metrics guides only
import { SYSTEM_DASHBOARD_PATH } from "../_utilities/screenshot-shared.mjs";

// For agents page only
import { clickAgentWithSchedule, clickAgentWithApprovals } from "../_utilities/screenshots/screenshot-helpers.mjs";
```

Only import what you actually use.

## Target object shape

```js
const dir = "your-guide-name"; // must match folder name exactly

export const targets = [
  {
    type: "element",            // always "element"
    selector: "...",            // Playwright selector — see Selector Patterns below
    filename: "my-screen.png", // snake_case, descriptive
    dir,                        // always the dir const
    path: "settings/people",   // URL path after BASE_URL (no leading slash)

    // Optional:
    clipToContent: true,        // clips screenshot to content height (use for tables/panels)
    contentEndSelector: "...",  // element that marks the bottom of the clip

    // Screenshot navigation (run once per target, idempotent):
    prepare: async (p) => { ... },

    // Video navigation (runs sequentially from previous step's end state):
    videoPrepare: async (p, cursor) => { ... },
  },
];
```

## Selector patterns

Use Playwright pseudo-selectors freely — they work here:

| UI element | Selector pattern |
|---|---|
| Modal/dialog | `[role="dialog"]:has(h2:has-text("Title"))` |
| Sheet/drawer | `[data-slot="sheet-content"]:has(h2:has-text("Title"))` |
| Table container | `div.overflow-auto.border-t:has(table:has(th:has-text("Column")))` |
| Quick filters / stat cards | `div.grid:has(div:has-text("Label1")):has(div:has-text("Label2"))` |
| Dropdown menu open | `[data-slot="dropdown-menu-content"]` |
| Section by heading | `div:has(h2:has-text("Section Title"))` |
| Named section ID | `[id="overview"]` |

Prefer semantic attributes (`role`, `data-slot`, `aria-label`) over fragile class chains.

## `prepare` — screenshot navigation

Each `prepare` runs independently (the page may be anywhere). Always:
1. Press Escape to close any open overlays
2. Navigate with `goto()` + `waitForLoadState("networkidle")`
3. Wait for the specific element/state needed

```js
prepare: async (p) => {
  await p.keyboard.press("Escape");
  await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 300));
  await p.goto(`${BASE_URL}/people`, { waitUntil: "domcontentloaded", timeout: 30000 });
  await p.waitForLoadState("networkidle");
  await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 2000));
  // click through to the required state...
  await p.getByRole("button", { name: "Add person" }).click();
  await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 1000));
},
```

## `videoPrepare` — video navigation

Runs sequentially: each step picks up where the previous left off. Use `clickWithCursor` for every click (it zooms in briefly and animates the cursor):

```js
videoPrepare: async (p, cursor) => {
  // Wait for something that proves we're in the right state
  await p.waitForSelector('[data-table-search="true"]', { state: "visible", timeout: 5000 });
  await clickWithCursor(p, cursor, 'button:has-text("Add person")', () =>
    p.getByRole("button", { name: "Add person" }).click(),
  );
  await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 800));
},
```

Rules for `videoPrepare`:
- Never full-navigate with `goto()` unless unavoidable — continue from prior step's state
- Always `waitFor` before interacting
- Use `clickWithCursor` for every user-visible click
- Short pauses (300–800 ms) after clicks; longer (1500–2000 ms) after page transitions

## `videoConfig` — add only when the guide has video

```js
export const videoConfig = {
  path: "people",   // initial navigation path for recording

  // Optional: reset UI state before recording starts
  preload: async (page) => {
    await page.waitForSelector("table tbody tr", { state: "visible", timeout: 15000 });
    await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 500));
  },
};
```

Omit `videoConfig` entirely for screenshot-only guides.

## Minimal example (screenshot-only guide)

```js
import { BASE_URL } from "../_utilities/screenshot-shared.mjs";

const dir = "managing-people";

export const targets = [
  {
    type: "element",
    selector: 'table:has(th:has-text("Department"))',
    filename: "people-list.png",
    dir,
    path: "people",
  },
  {
    type: "element",
    selector: '[role="dialog"]:has(h2:has-text("Invite person"))',
    filename: "invite-dialog.png",
    dir,
    path: "people",
    prepare: async (p) => {
      await p.keyboard.press("Escape");
      await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 300));
      await p.goto(`${BASE_URL}/people`, { waitUntil: "domcontentloaded", timeout: 30000 });
      await p.waitForLoadState("networkidle");
      await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 2000));
      await p.getByRole("button", { name: "Invite" }).click();
      await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    },
  },
];
```

## After creating the blueprint

Run `pnpm run studio` from `mintlify-docs/` to verify the guide now shows `✓` in the Blueprint column and the expected screenshot count is correct.
